Yes. Within your 14 elective courses (70 credits) you must take:

- at least 20 credits (4 courses) of advanced-level courses;
- no more than 15 credits (3 courses) of introductory-level courses;
- at least 3 courses and at least 20 credits at 3000-level.

Your 8 elective skills (20 credits) and 4 elective projects (20 credits) complete the elective space. Keep an eye on these minimums early, because advanced and 3000-level courses need prerequisites and cannot all be left to the final semesters.
